From c254eeebcf6469874813178c84a11b531b904e76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: regksem <regksem@tuta.io>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:02:04 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add cmd_ban module with proxy-wide bans

Adds a bundled command module providing /gban, /gtempban, /gunban and /gbanlist.
Bans target a player name and, when the player is online, their last-known IP;
both are checked on PreLoginEvent so banned players are denied entry, and online
matches are kicked immediately. Temporary bans expire automatically and are
pruned on load and lookup.

State is persisted to bans.yml and the deny messages are configurable via
config.yml, both in the module's data folder. The module is shipped inside the
jar like the other command modules and enabled by default (modules.yml v4).

